title: Thomas Meilstrup’s CV
text:
Bioinformatician and Musician.


Intern at BYU studying respiratory diseases with Chantel Sloan-Aagard


Social Media Management. Computer Skills – Introductory Python, R, & SQL. Capable Leader and Teacher. Quick Learner. Researcher



Genetics, Molecular Biology, Biochemistry.




Fall 2017 - Spring 2021 Chaparral High School – Parker, CO
FALL 2021 – SPRING 2022, Fall 2024 -- PRESENT Brigham Young University - Idaho – Rexburg, ID

Currently Majoring in Biology with an Emphasis in Bioinformatics.
Member of the PhD Research Honor Society.
Participating in an extracurricular research team doing PCR diagnostics for metabolic syndrome and Least Chub range testing.




Boy Scouts
2017 Eagle Scout
Chaparral Band
2021 - John Philip Sousa Band Award - Senior Outstanding Band Student - Outstanding Citizenship Award






JUNE 2024 – SEPTEMBER 2024 Managed drive-through transactions. Assisted in closing most nights.



MAY 2023 – MAY 2024 Led and Managed social media teams while a volunteer missionary. Teams included Analytics, Graphic Design, Messaging, Video Production, and others.



MAY 2022 – MAY 2024 Effectively provided humanitarian assistance and training to several thousand people over a two-year period in San Diego CA.



SPRING 2021 – SPRING 2022 Cleaned movie theatres, sold concessions and tickets.



DECEMBER 2019 Seasonal job wrapping, facing, and weighing hams and turkeys



JUNE 2019 – AUGUST 2019 Bagged Groceries, Faced Shelves, Gathered carts



SUMMER 2017 – SUMMER 2021 Staffed the snack shack at the pool on a volunteer basis each summer as a fundraiser for the Chaparral Marching Band.



SPRING 2016 – SPRING 2021 Planned, executed, and hosted various library events each month.



SUMMER 2015 – SUMMER 2019 Led sectionals for elementary students at a weeklong camp every year.
